-- EPS in the First Quarter of ’13 for S&P 500 Stocks by Industry
-- B y   W e n d y   S o o n g
-- 2013-06-12T20:37:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-06-12/eps-in-the-first-quarter-of-13-for-s-p-500-stocks-by-industry.html
Here are the cumulative earnings
per share results for the first quarter of 2013 for  Standard & Poor’s (SPX) 
500 Index stocks broken down into 24 industries. Within industries,
companies are ranked by year-over-year percent changes.  Profit figures are based on income from continuing operations
excluding some gains and losses. Industry averages are  share-weighted 
percentage changes of year-over-year comparisons.  Earnings estimates  are
provided by Bloomberg.  
NM -- The calculations of percentage changes between profit and loss
and vice versa are not meaningful, hence not calculated.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Wendy Soong in  New York  at   csoong@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
